stylometry: Simulation models allow multiple variables to be tested through one problem very easily. They can also test the sensitivity of different variables in a problem. It is very beneficial to use simulations in business because they provide input for making decisions without the price tag. For example, if a supermarket wanted to test the profitability of adding 3 cash registers to their store, they could either purchase the expensive equipment and test how it affects their operating income, however if the result is negative, they are stuck with the extra equipment. With a simulation model, the store data can be used to simulate the new checkout lines into the model and discover the effect on the supermarket's business without the extra costs.
